Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.78,0:00:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The implications of knowing the distribution of the levels of consciousness in the world are\Nthe purpose of it is the science of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.00,0:01:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no science of peace, no science of diplomacy.\NAnd we just invented it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.64,0:01:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What we do is we calibrate the level of consciousness.\NThis is international relationships. You can use it in politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.67,0:01:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In politics, you can say, what is the average consciousness level of the voter?\NTherefore, where must our platform be to appeal to the voter?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.07,0:01:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't that simple?\NThe people with the biggest mouths are down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.14,0:01:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The electorate is up here.\NShaking your fist with emotion doesn't appeal to these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.14,0:01:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They think you need a doctor.\NSo it's applicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's applicable to politics, to business, to advertising.\NYou know, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.09,0:02:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is your target audience?\NAnd what does our advertisement calibrate at?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.54,0:02:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I see idiot advertisements out there.\NHere's this big chunky guy with little blue wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.31,0:02:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And pregnant women are wandering back and forth.\NThere's all kinds of phenomena going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.31,0:02:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's three initials that keep coming across.\NI don't know what they stand for.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.33,0:02:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle soup.\NNuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.55,0:02:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this stand for?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.21,0:02:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate is at 135.\NI'm seeing millions spent on that stupid ad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.21,0:02:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, all right.\NSo use your advertising budget wisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.28,0:02:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your energies wisely.\NUse your efforts wisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.28,0:02:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your program for a school district.\NHere it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.88,0:02:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you have to sell it to?\NHere's the school board here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.88,0:02:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the parents here.\NHere's the community here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.97,0:02:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is your program if you want to win?\NInternational diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.02,0:03:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We already gave examples this morning of why trying to sell democracy in parts of the world is idiotic and stupid.\NGiving every man equally a vote, you got to be out of your mind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds stupid.\NWhat we consider to be reality in other cultures is called stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.87,0:03:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sucker and dumb.\NAnd they wouldn't be caught dead telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.87,0:03:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean they're told the truth?\NTold the truth in court?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTake them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.75,0:03:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize he's dangerous?\NYou know what they do with truth tellers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.31,0:03:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They take them out.\NThe boys take you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.59,0:03:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot be trusted.\NOnce you get, you're at a 180 with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.78,0:03:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's America at 421.\NAnd these are the calibrated levels of various countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.74,0:04:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see, therefore,\Nwhat kind of a program, what kind of languaging,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see what the prevailing sense of reality is.\NBy knowing that, by writing about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.13,0:04:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of poking in a people's face by publishing it,\Nprovocatively,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.04,0:04:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it is possible to have a science of diplomacy\Nthat might give you some chances of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.04,0:04:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Chances of success.\NYou have to, before you can sell something,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.19,0:04:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to know who you're dealing with.\NWho you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.19,0:04:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That tells you how to phrase it, how to present it,\Nhow to be with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.68,0:04:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also precludes the egotism\Nof thinking that our truth is superior to other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.77,0:05:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the abrasive quality of Americanism in the world,\Nwhich has always been an embarrassment to me since World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.93,0:05:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So.\NAnd to which the French reacted strongly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.93,0:05:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and they haven't recovered from World War II either.\NDe Gaulle, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.48,0:05:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He's saving France, yeah, right.\NHe was elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.14,0:05:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He was elsewhere.\NElsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.66,0:05:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't a freedom fighter in Paris.\NOkay, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.66,0:05:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This tells us who we are.\NThis could be our company here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.05,0:05:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Walmart.\NEverybody hates that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.05,0:05:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmart haters.\NThey're big, successful, and they're American.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.30,0:05:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NPlus they make a profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.18,0:05:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Man.\NThat is hateful, ain't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:06:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Like it or not, bite the bullet.\NHere's Walmart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.72,0:06:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Stick that where the sun don't shine.\NWell, you can calibrate all the companies you invest in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.18,0:06:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Take out your stock portfolio, and you'll be selling and buying soon.\NYeah, all the ones that collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We were working on the book back in, what, 2002 or something.\NWe did all the major corporations in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.54,0:06:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was a lot of them under 200, you know.\NUnder 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.75,0:06:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Which we didn't print or publish.\NBut we didn't have the stock in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.94,0:06:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But we told people to sell it.\NThere's a lot of companies that didn't do too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.77,0:06:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,World Comm and all.\NSo, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.06,0:06:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Appearance is the stock value.\NEssence is what the company calibrates at.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.42,0:07:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all your stocks.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.02,0:07:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not greed, you see.\NIf you demonize the ego, you get paralyzed with greed and guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you have a responsibility, especially if you're destined to be enlightened,\Nto be the steward of your assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.68,0:07:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about winning.\NGet out of the solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.49,0:07:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Solar plexus is about winning and fear of losing and greed and all that.\NAnd even if you succeed, you end up with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.64,0:07:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You end up with guilt.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your increase is the price of somebody else's decrease.\NNo, you have to re-contextualize your assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What are your assets?\NTime, how many years you got left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.30,0:07:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How many hours in a day.\NAssets, financial.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Personality-wise.\NIf you're six foot six and fast on the court,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.30,0:08:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you have an obligation to respect that capacity, that talent.\NIf you're good at taking shorthand, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.02,0:08:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your talents, your abilities, your assets.\NInstead of greed now, you respect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're grateful for them and you handle them with respect and honor.\NYou owe that respect to yourself and to your destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't waste years.\NPlaying around in casinos and things when there's far more important things to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.25,0:08:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I say don't waste time exploring the astral domains.\NNew age-ism, all kinds of psychics, healers, peddlers, circus clowns on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Play at it if you want.\NSo you blow a few more lifetimes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:09:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Except they're more clever at it than you are.\NTherefore, it's arrogance that makes you think you can play with the astral domains and not get singed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.01,0:09:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know of anybody who's played with the astral domain that has not been singed.\NNobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.70,0:09:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been at it for eons.\NThe slightest hesitation tells you exactly why you're going to be a buyer of sweetness and light.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I have come from another dimension to tell you.\NOf the revelations of Whoopah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.54,0:09:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The ancient mysteries of Whoopah.\NYou see, you just got glamorized, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.17,0:09:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause it's from a different dimension, you're automatically glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.55,0:09:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The child in you is still enamored of magic.\NOh, in a physical universe, you can get a psychic reading that says,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.49,0:10:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I see your grandmother came from Ireland.\NOoh, shit, she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.64,0:10:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How does she know that?\NAnd your father, who's still in the lodge on the other side, wants you to so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.37,0:10:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, that's a fact.\NYou just got hooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.03,0:10:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hook, line, and sinker.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.37,0:10:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all the information about you is public domain.\NDon't you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.37,0:10:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got through telling you.\NYou can calibrate the level of truth of anything that's ever existed in time, energy, or anywhere, even a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.37,0:10:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Being psychic is nothing at all.\NThere's a whole level of consciousness where your psychic is all hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.11,0:10:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the mid-500s, as this kundalini energy comes up, you develop the so-called siddhis, S-I-D-D-H-I-S, paranormal capacities.\NThe kundalini energy flows through you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.09,0:11:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You become psychic, clairvoyant.\NYou can go anywhere out of body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.62,0:11:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go inside of something, read it, come back out again.\NI did it in front of witnesses all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.75,0:11:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in the box?\NI'll tell you in a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.75,0:11:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, hello.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.00,0:11:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know?\NBecause I went there, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.01,0:11:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think I'm paying the money to learn how to do it for?\NSo that is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.89,0:11:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you get mystified and impressed and glamorized by natural domains.\NSome of those entities have been there, I hate to tell you, they were old at the time of Mesopotamia, and Mesopotamia was their high point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.53,0:11:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget how expert people can be at what they do.\NI was a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.14,0:12:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the biggest practice in the United States, practiced 50 years.\NBy the time a person made the appointment, I already knew what was wrong with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I already got it.\NI want to see you on Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?\NWell, I've been getting this and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.52,0:12:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already got what it is.\NIf it's a patient I'm treating, my office, there was a wooden hallway leading into the main clinic and rows of offices and labs and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,To get to my office, they had to walk down the row past all the labs and offices and all.\NThey walked across the floor to my office, which was somewhat remote.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.99,0:12:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,By the sound of the footsteps, I can already tell you whether they're better or worse.\NI can already tell you what I'm going to have to do with the dose of the med.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.40,0:12:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I already got it.\NI got them on the wrong med.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.70,0:12:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I better try something different.\NThere's no one working.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.62,0:12:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,People are really expert.\NThere are people, by the time you say hello, they already read you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.89,0:12:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Entities on the other side have been doing that for eons.\NA little naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to pay your ticket and get your order read.\NGive me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could do that without getting entranced, okay.\NBut you're going to get entranced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already entranced by the magic of it, by the fact that you went there for a reading, aren't you?\NThey already got you by curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the evolution of consciousness goes through evolution, including the spiritual aspect of your own development.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.46,0:13:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is spiritual begins as naive, childish, the wonderment of it all.\NI went to see this psychic, and she said, your uncle got hit in a motorcycle accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, just wow.\NEverybody know that experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.39,0:13:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Liars.\NTruth tellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.07,0:14:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's had that experience.\NYou haven't been glamorized by a psychic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.46,0:14:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You ain't lived yet.\NI'll see you later, and I'm going to read your future, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.58,0:14:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get what happened.\NI can get what happened and where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause the infinite field of consciousness includes everything known about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.37,0:14:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo I just thought I'd tell you a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NGo on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.52,0:14:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?\NI got five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.75,0:14:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one.\NThis is the rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.41,0:14:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not only the percentage of happiness, but to see what makes a person happy here\Nwill make you feel guilty up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.41,0:14:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And vice versa.\NSo you have a reverse morality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.58,0:15:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, to not get is a matter of shame and guilt.\NHere, to get creates guilt because you think, oh, that's my solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.89,0:15:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I was wanting gain.\NThat's the vanity of the ego, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.89,0:15:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Lord, please help me get over that.\NWanting to win the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.00,0:15:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNext.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NLevel of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.39,0:15:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And related happiness.\NWhich we saw on the other one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.39,0:15:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next slide.\NThat was, skip that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.13,0:15:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's incongruity.\NWe'll skip this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.13,0:15:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Skip this one.\NSkip this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.19,0:15:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's him saying, I should have left the body.\NWhy the hell didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.14,0:15:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe'll stop here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.14,0:15:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll stop the slides here.\NWe'll resume later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.62,0:15:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And see, by knowing the basic dictums.\NThe basic truths.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.62,0:16:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you don't have to go there.\NYou'll have to sacrifice the kick out of the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.89,0:16:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go over Niagara Falls in a barrel for kicks.\NAnd if you're spiritually aligned, you can't afford it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.83,0:16:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't afford it.\NWhat turns you off about doing that is the disrespect for the divinity of his own creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.60,0:16:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He has so little respect for yourself that you would put yourself in such extreme injury.\NFor both death and damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as forcing the commitment of society to come in and save you.\NAnd then bury you at tax payers cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.26,0:16:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the sheer disrespect of it.\NFor the transitory solar plexus kick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.33,0:17:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual evolution does require somewhat declining.\NAnd some of the novelties and kicks that come along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Be thankful then and respect that your destiny is to become enlightened.\NThat's the destiny of 90% of the people here in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.57,0:17:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rest of the people are going to go back to the bar.\NAnd come back next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.57,0:17:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NWe'll see you after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.68,0:17:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What time is lunch?\NWhat time do we resume?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NWe have an hour and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.95,0:17:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NI prepare people for their inevitable future.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.70,0:18:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We know what everybody's future is here.\NAt least 90%.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.70,0:18:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,10% are going to chicken out.\NSmart chicken out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NTo be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.47,0:18:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd to be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.53,0:18:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You've chosen the way to God.\NAnd this is going to realign your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.53,0:18:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The sequencing is not going to be the same as it would have been.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.66,0:18:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you prepare for it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.\NWe also can talk about what spirituality is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot that is not.\NAnd it's labeled as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.98,0:18:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Peddled as such.\NMerchandised as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NAs you know from some of the ways I communicate,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:19:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,spirituality does not mean a feat.\NHearts and flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.70,0:19:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're all going to be happy now.\NAnd we'll all sing a song.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll all sing a song like this is the maypole and this is kindergarten.\NNow, you know where the sun don't shine, that's English.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.75,0:19:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, spirituality does not require being a feat and delicate\Nand like a wispy little flower singing hymns around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.05,0:19:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It requires strength, courage, valor as you get to extremely high levels.\NIt requires the capacity to experience actually physical pain and various agonies
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.85,0:19:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and to allow nothing to deter you along the way.\NSo that is anything but a feat, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:20:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes everything you've got.\NAnd without divine help, it's not even possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.74,0:20:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Not possible.\NIt's not possible to calibrate below 200 and become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.94,0:20:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have the karma, go for it.\NWe were talking about the level.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.29,0:20:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It emerges around the level that the people call sainthood,\Naround the high 500s, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.94,0:20:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When that kundalini starts to flow.\NWe didn't talk about that energy, did we?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NWe didn't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.88,0:20:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But the many of the things that you pick up later in the astral circus\Nwere actually phenomena that were derived from those states
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.56,0:20:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because...\NYou feel this exquisite sensation running up your spine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:21:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Not having read anything about kundalini.\NI didn't get glamorized by it, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.45,0:21:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there's just an exquisite sense of pleasure\Nthat runs up your back, runs up your whole back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.31,0:21:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it runs up into your head, like into your brain.\NAnd if you focus on the left side of the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.06,0:21:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it tends to go in that side.\NSo this exquisite sensation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.19,0:21:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a flowing energy, is all I can say.\NAnd it's extremely exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.33,0:21:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you really value that state\Nbecause it has that quality that goes with it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.75,0:21:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've never experienced before,\Nexcept maybe in some incredible psychedelic conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.65,0:21:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or states of intoxication.\NWell, you got a glimpse of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.69,0:22:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's why they're intoxicating.\NYou're not intoxicated by the substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.30,0:22:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're intoxicated by the quality of subjectivity.\NWhen you're beautifully still with the right combination of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.88,0:22:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the music is perfect,\Nyou are in like an incredible state.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.11,0:22:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If only it were possible to stay there.\NBut it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.45,0:22:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, having once experienced that state prematurely,\Nnow you can...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.13,0:22:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You go into anguish and despair\Nbecause when you have to stop the substance,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.91,0:22:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that state is no longer accessible.\NBut now, you have experienced that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.64,0:22:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore, nothing less will ever do in overtime.\NTherefore, at least energy 540,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.05,0:23:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which is supplied by the 12-step groups,\Nyou begin to feel naturally that which was artificial before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.68,0:23:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That condition keeps coming.\NIt's going from unconditional lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.35,0:23:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, that energy begins to flow.\NAround 560, around 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's exquisite.\NAlso, the energy is not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.26,0:23:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a quality of phenomena.\NAnd the quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.71,0:23:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the things the energy does is\Nyou become clairaudient, clairvoyant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.95,0:23:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can go inside a box.\NWe were talking about it at lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.50,0:23:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there's a message in a closed box.\NYou can look at the box, project yourself in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,read it, and come back out and say, it says, hello.\NAnd they open the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.08,0:23:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a thing that says, hello.\NNo problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.84,0:23:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can go where you've never been\Nand know exactly how to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.69,0:24:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All you do is hold the destination in mind\Nand you automatically see exactly where to park
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.04,0:24:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of Lincoln Center.\NAnd as you get there, the first car on the right-hand side,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.67,0:24:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the nearest, most wonderful parking place of all time,\Nin front of Lincoln Center, is the Lincoln Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.30,0:24:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you drive up, they pull out and you drive in.\NAnd it's all normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.48,0:24:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Life just unveils that way.\NAnd that's why they call it the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.35,0:24:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because that becomes normal, normal.\NAnd not that you have an expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.25,0:24:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not, there's nobody trying to make it happen.\NThe phenomena occur of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.65,0:24:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the side phenomena of the cities is,\NI've described before, it would like flow out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.77,0:24:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It would like flow out.\NIt would like flow out from the heart chakra.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.27,0:24:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And it would go places and bring about healings\Nand the miraculous and, you know, phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.04,0:24:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that from the Newtonian paradigm would be called miraculous.\NIn its own paradigm, it's natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.23,0:25:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But outside of that paradigm, they'd say,\Nhow did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.13,0:25:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you didn't do it, you know.\NThat's the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.93,0:25:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena is of its own.\NIt's a divine energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.58,0:25:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always got that the people to whom it flowed had been praying.\NIt would be like you're an antenna.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.52,0:25:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the car is turned upside down as you turn the corner.\NAnd the highway, the wheels are actually still spinning right here on I-17.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.38,0:25:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you feel the energy shoot out and shoot into the people within the car.\NAnd then all of a sudden, the energy stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.67,0:25:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you got the people in the car were praying, dear God, please help us.\NThat energy just shoots directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.76,0:25:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're like the nearest sending radio antenna.\NAnd the program goes to them, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.50,0:26:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not any personal self.\NThat fact is obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.31,0:26:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It performs.\NI could keep you the rest of the afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.77,0:26:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell you how the phenomena it would do.\NIt fixed 100-watt hi-fi amplifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.03,0:26:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy was going there, and the amplifier was blown out.\NAnd somebody said, there's something wrong with the amplifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.09,0:26:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, oh, yeah?\NAll of a sudden, the amplifier go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.98,0:26:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy said, I saw that.\NThat's what actually happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.11,0:26:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Radio repair, he said, I saw that.\NHe says, that was a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.03,0:26:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, somehow the subject of the course of miracles comes up.\NAnd I said, oh, it's just what the world calls the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.84,0:26:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow, he says, I'm really interested in that.\NI had one copy, extra copy left of the course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.00,0:26:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, here, here, this is what you're looking for.\NAnd he said, oh, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.42,0:26:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how just one thing?\NI mean, the only reason he came there
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.61,0:27:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,was to make contact with the course of miracles and get that.\NAnd the phenomena just was a phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.42,0:27:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Those phenomena happen of their own, yeah.\NThe trick is, don't be glamorized by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.61,0:27:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try and sell them and realize that they are not you.\NSo somebody we were talking earlier about,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.81,0:27:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,some entities on the other side, you see,\Nthe mistake they made because they didn't have a teacher that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.44,0:27:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,forewarned them in advance not to get glamorized or personalized\Nthe cities when they arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.18,0:27:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They lack that education.\NTherefore, they're innocent by virtue of not
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.98,0:27:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,having known the difference.\NBut when they come on, you realize it's equality,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.44,0:27:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not personal.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.31,0:27:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,own them as a personal power, then you\Nfreeze it there and now you become a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.69,0:28:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,psychic, you know, eons after eons, you\Nknow, you're giving readings in the year
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.91,0:28:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,892 and you're still giving them, because\Nyou're stuck in the glamorization and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.75,0:28:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of that, you know, seeing the\Ndefinition of yourself is a psychic
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.80,0:28:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,clairvoyant and all that. So everybody in\Nthe high 500 has become psychic
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.16,0:28:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,clairvoyant, I mean there's nothing,\Neverybody's telepathic and in that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.81,0:28:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,state you always know what question the\Nperson has in their mind, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.72,0:28:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what they're thinking, I mean\Nit's just natural to the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.00,0:28:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody's telepathic. You can\Nexperience that even way before the high
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.25,0:28:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,fives, 500s, so-called silent retreats, or\Nyou go away for a weekend somebody's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.07,0:28:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,house with half a dozen people and you\Ndon't speak from, you know, Friday till
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.33,0:28:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday morning or something, everybody\Nbecomes telepathic, I mean it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.70,0:28:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing,\Neverybody very quickly too, within 24
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.77,0:28:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,hours, you know, you think salt and at the\Ntenor table and then just as you think
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.27,0:29:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it, somebody hands you the salt shaker, I\Nmean it's normal. So it's not a unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.31,0:29:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's when you get out of the linear, the\Nnonlinear takes over. So a lot of things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.01,0:29:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,are known by the field and it's not the\Nperson, it's the field, and so that was the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.75,0:29:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,precaution.\NAbout getting glamorized by all that, you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.44,0:29:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,see, the other thing about truth is it\Ndoesn't need to be glamorized. So let's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.94,0:29:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,do the next, let's do the next slide, you\Ngot another slide? That's how the professor
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.77,0:29:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,knew he was about to lose his\Nposition, he ran out of slides. So that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.50,0:29:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,brought up then, by consciousness\Ncalibration plus the knowingness from
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.05,0:30:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,within.\NThere is an awareness of spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.53,0:30:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity, what is integrous and what is\Nnot integrous, and you can sense it, but
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.03,0:30:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning, if you don't believe it,\Nyou can calibrate it. The calibration
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.31,0:30:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,level of various things then, by\Nexperience, having been up and down the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.09,0:30:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,scale, then you develop what's called\Ndiscernment, the opening of the third eye
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.47,0:30:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Buddhic body is called discernment.\NYou'd be able to be, you sense the real
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.49,0:30:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,from that which is searching for\Nadvantage and gain, you know. That which
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.29,0:30:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the real is all that is and has\Nnothing to gain, and then by that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.09,0:30:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,identify it. Nothing to gain, doesn't have\Na program going for itself, isn't trying
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.84,0:31:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to promote, isn't trying to proselytize,\Nisn't trying to glamorize, isn't trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.77,0:31:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.\NSeduction, that's called seduction, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.02,0:31:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth, because it's completely satisfied by the fulfillment of its own potential,\Nhas no gain, doesn't need conversation, doesn't need votes, doesn't need members,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.95,0:31:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't need to proselytize, doesn't need to sign you up,\Ndoesn't need to control you or intimidate you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.70,0:31:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or pose hypothetical threats whereby to control you.\NSo he's not interested in your sex life, your personal life,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.08,0:31:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what you wear, eat, dress, and where you go, what you have for dinner.\NDoesn't care whether you're a vegetarian, whether you give up sex,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.07,0:31:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or sex is your lifestyle.\NSomebody's got to do something, I mean, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.76,0:32:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's got to repopulate the earth, you know.\NThey've got nothing better to do anyway at that age, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.94,0:32:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody serves in their own way, so.\NYou get called out of stud service over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.22,0:32:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The world has to get along without your divine gifts.\NThe responsibility of the teacher, then, is to give certain understandings
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.10,0:32:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that preclude their later being taken advantage of and falling off.\NI always feel sorry for fallen gurus because I see the mistake they made,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.61,0:32:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I know why they made it,\Nand I know the teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.40,0:33:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know the teaching that they were missing.\NTherefore, my obligation is to share with you all that I know about the,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.07,0:33:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, likelihoods along the way because all likelihoods are held in place.\NOn one side, there's the temptation that gives it attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.11,0:33:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side, there's a loss or a pain that is the aversion.\NSo we'll get to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.74,0:33:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last slide today, the dualities of attractions and aversions.\NHaving aligned yourself now with the truth, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.15,0:33:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you become dedicated to it, and the way, now, what is the way to where you want to go?\NYou've picked your destiny, and you've committed yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.58,0:33:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and now, how do you know which is the right roadmap?\NAnd therefore, I've tried to provide a reliable roadmap.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.94,0:33:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done some of them before.\NWe've done some of them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.74,0:33:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But some people here are new, and it's all new to them.\NThat which is true is true all the time, everywhere, for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.19,0:34:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, every advanced mystic is the same, no matter what century,\Nno matter what part of the world, it's always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.11,0:34:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only one absolute reality, and it reveals itself in various dimensions.\NTherefore, the inner subjective awareness and experience of an enlightened master in,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.53,0:34:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say, 4000 BC in India should be the same as 1936 in Chicago.\NThere's no difference at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.94,0:34:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence shines forth, unmistakably has what it is.\NIt's true at all times, all places.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.07,0:34:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody that possesses the truth.\NSo, you know, there's various claims.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.32,0:34:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We got the truth.\NWe got the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.50,0:35:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And they shoot each other and blow each other up.\NIf you don't blow my truth, I'm going to blow you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.03,0:35:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They do.\NThey're probably doing it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.23,0:35:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to have something to do.\NYou blow up infidels, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.78,0:35:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep you busy.\NThe world's full of infidels.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.98,0:35:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If your trip is blowing up infidels, your life's work is cut out for you.\NGet up early, go to bed late.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.96,0:35:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Making bombs and all the fuses.\NThey work their fingers to the bone making bombs to blow up children with.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.09,0:35:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless them.\NUniversality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.26,0:35:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's always true, not exclusive, all-inclusive, not secretive, and not sectarian.\NNobody owes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.71,0:35:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's got an exclusive.\NThere's nothing to peddle and sell because the truth is obvious, clear, available to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.21,0:36:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone, anytime.\NAll they need is by integrous dedication, they'll really re-experience it themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.51,0:36:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's always the same.\NThere's nothing secret about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.67,0:36:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no mystery about it.\NIn fact, all those who experience it, they're going to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.07,0:36:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to experience the truth, proclaim it.\NThe Buddha said, it is the most wondrous of the wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.19,0:36:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone precludes it.\NHe didn't keep it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.21,0:36:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh man, I really got enlightened and too bad about you.\NNo, he rejected the Hindu teachings which he thought were incorrect, bowed his inner
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.48,0:36:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,muse and arrived at the ultimate state.\NHe then proclaimed it to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.73,0:36:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one thing.\NOne thing that one does is to proclaim its pristine excellence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.48,0:36:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no mystery.\NTherefore, there's nothing to sell about it, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.84,0:37:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is available to all and the doorway to the truth is open to all.\NWith no secrets, there's nothing to sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.44,0:37:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no stratification, you know, junior master, middle master, higher master, super\Nmaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.50,0:37:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.65,0:37:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can jump you from master to super master and it's only 5,000 for the workshop.\NAnybody want to give me five grand, I'll make you a super master right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.26,0:37:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NI'll tell you what, better yet, I want to make everybody here a super master and now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.82,0:37:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you better live up to that title.\NYou are now all going to be masters in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.32,0:37:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NEveryone here already has the energy of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.36,0:37:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NAnd the reason you're here is to shine that forth through generations to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.05,0:37:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the purpose of enlightenment.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.05,0:38:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open to all.\NNo secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.69,0:38:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is hidden, sold.\NThere are no magical formulas or mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.78,0:38:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What is there about a mystery?\NI know it and you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.15,0:38:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you who's throwing the mysteries.\NKindergarteners.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.44,0:38:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a secret, Sylvia.\NI've got one too, Betty.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.07,0:38:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Betty, let's form a club.\NThe secret club.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.55,0:38:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll call it the Triple Bunny Club.\NThey got three members.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.65,0:38:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we'll keep it a secret who's members.\NWe'll have a sign like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.57,0:38:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Symbols and signs and secrets.\NOaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.23,0:38:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NSwear upon your Oz book that you will not relate to anybody that you're a secret member of this society.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.69,0:38:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wizard of Oz.\NPurpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.19,0:39:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to gain or lose.\NOnce the bowl is full, there's nothing more it would want, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.26,0:39:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no difference between yourself and that which is all that is.\NConsequently, it's a nuisance to have to own something.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.88,0:39:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's really a drag.\NIt really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.36,0:39:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To have to own it and get legal papers and the whole business.\NIt's nicer to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.17,0:39:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You own it.\NWhen I need a piano, I'll borrow it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.15,0:39:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you got to...\NYou got to own all the pianos in the world and life gets heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.00,0:39:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-sectarian.\NTherefore, it's not limited geographically or culturally or ethnically.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.73,0:39:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the religions, you know, became ethnic, secularized.\NThey really became...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.21,0:40:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll tell you what the error was and it is very prominent today.\NInstead of worshiping God, they worship the religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.05,0:40:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Religionism.\NIt replaces God.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.88,0:40:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It releases truth.\NYou're worshiping the priests and the holy places.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.86,0:40:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to walk where Baba walked.\NI mean, people really, they go all across the planet to walk where Baba walked.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.61,0:40:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing about Baba there anymore at all.\NIf you calibrate the holy lands, you'll find they're about 182 or 210 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.55,0:40:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing holy about the holy lands at all.\NPeople have been blasting each other to death on the holy lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.40,0:40:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to walk over the dry blood.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.13,0:40:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what isn't a space or locality or personage is nothing that's owned.\NThere's nothing, no ritual you have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.51,0:41:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NTo be a member of our class, you got to say regimentary backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.13,0:41:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's why you have such a small class.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.17,0:41:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's no code words.\NThere's no secrets, non-sectarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.01,0:41:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't depend on opinion.\NTruth is non-linear, not subject to opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.34,0:41:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Not subject to opinion.\NSo, the downside of religion then is actually, if you look at it, you'll see the politicalization of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.32,0:41:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the non-integrist ego uses religion for its own non-integrist purposes,\Nto control other people, to gain property, to get money out of the peasants,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.34,0:42:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to control the serfs.\NAnd the serfdoms, the fiefdoms, to hand out the titles, it seeks worldly, secular power.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.61,0:42:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It glamorizes itself and it aggrandizes itself.\NIt gives itself incredible titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.05,0:42:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Emperor of all of creation, I am the emperor of Europe.\NAnd that's when Napoleon went from 460 down to 160 or whatever he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.44,0:42:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for the people.\NAnd that's when Napoleon went from 460 down to 160 or whatever he was, for the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.40,0:42:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when Napoleon went from 460 down to 160 or whatever he was, for the people.\NNapoleon was incredibly integrist, contributed a great deal to Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.11,0:42:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when he crowned himself emperor, he defied the sovereignty of God,\Nbecause the ruler came via divinity, and divinity in those days was known via the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.92,0:43:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was the pope that declared you emperor.\NWhen Napoleon declared himself emperor, and crowned himself, his consciousness calibration went from 460 to 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.03,0:43:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,450 or 60, down to 160, and therefore at the Battle of Waterloo. At Waterloo,\NNapoleon was counting on the power he once had. You know, he was a magical,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.71,0:43:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,mystical midget, right? I mean, when Napoleon stood in front of his troops,\Nhis troops adored him. They adored him. He was a wondrous and marvelous human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.80,0:43:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and I loved Napoleon before he crowned himself. He was a\Ngreat figure, you know, but in that sodoing, he usurped the power of God as
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.80,0:43:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,represented in the culture of its time and he found really the sovereignty of\NGod. So, and then at Waterloo, of course, he was mincemeat. Okay. No requirements or
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.42,0:44:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,demands. You don't have to promise anything. No membership.\NYou don't have to sign anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.30,0:44:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to take any secret oaths.\NThere's no regulations, no rules or conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.73,0:44:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody gets expelled.\NPrison can screw up really awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.32,0:44:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't care.\NSay you're sorry that you killed those eight people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.13,0:44:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on now.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.86,0:44:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, come back.\NA decent regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.40,0:44:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A decent regret.\NWhat stands traditionally is all that's really necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.65,0:44:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to grovel, because that's another ego game.\NYou know, you've groveled your way through, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.92,0:44:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how many pairs of knee pads in front of the cathedral.\NI mean, what a grand display.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.26,0:44:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you flagellate yourself, you know.\NI mean, that's all the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.40,0:44:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all ego drama.\NNon-binding.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.59,0:44:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to sign any oaths, contracts.\NFreedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.92,0:45:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's free to come and go as they wish.\NOh, commonality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.07,0:45:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's special.\NPeople have a function to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.71,0:45:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Function to do.\NI got to give the lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.94,0:45:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if I don't give the lectures, who's going to give them?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.21,0:45:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to.\NSo, you are what you do, what purpose you serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.69,0:45:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NBut nobody's like ooh la la by virtue of a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.15,0:45:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you're the sixth patriarch of the eighth descendant\Nof the third incarnation of Baba Bum Bum.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.40,0:45:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NFirst of all, the truth is non-linear, so you can't transmit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.30,0:45:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no linear, linearity by which to transmit it.\NIt doesn't get transmitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.51,0:45:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You bump into the Buddha, you were ready for the enlightenment,\Nyou got the enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.57,0:46:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't transmitted from him to you.\NYou walked into the field by karmic design.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.94,0:46:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't like a this Buddha gives enlightenment to a that.\NDevate.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.92,0:46:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.61,0:46:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference is there's a difference.\NThere's a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.36,0:46:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a difference.\NThere's a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.53,0:46:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Devate's vibration and frequency rises to a certain level and welcomes that.\NAnd then in the presence of the teacher, becomes energized by that aura, that vibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.32,0:46:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know when you'll need it.\NIt could be ten lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.53,0:46:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it could be tomorrow.\NJust as your car turns over, as it goes off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.46,0:46:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the third flip, you got it, baby.\NYou watch the car roll along in the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.78,0:46:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You go.\NBig deal, big deal, big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.13,0:46:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom.\NCommonality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.98,0:47:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspirational.\NIt's partly the job of a teacher to try to present information in such a way that it is cognizant of that which is listening to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.34,0:47:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one thing to say it well and good for yourself.\NIt's one thing to be integrous and to state the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.59,0:47:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't ignore the audience.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.88,0:47:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say things.\NI say things that are not considered spiritual, yeah, amongst your feet, you know, where the sun don't shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.01,0:47:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That ain't fancy language.\NBut that's one reason we have a lot of men in our groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.19,0:47:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of, well, a lot of motivational speakers.\NYou see the, you know, you see the video, you taste them on TV, and they're like 90% women.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.92,0:47:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guys are sitting there like they've just been dragged to the opera, you know.\NYou look at the next one, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.11,0:48:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the guy sitting there.\NKind of look attentive to please her, and he's being polite to the speaker, and it's vaguely interesting, but it's not really his, his thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.94,0:48:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It ain't his shtick, you know.\NSo I also speak to men, because there's also men out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.00,0:48:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't live in the world of daisies and flowers.\NThey're living the world of make a mistake, and you're no longer president of this corporation, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.26,0:48:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay.\NFreedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.98,0:48:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Free to come and go.\NCommonality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.98,0:48:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Recognition is the consequence of what you do and what you become.\NWe inspire each other by the example of who we have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.34,0:48:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not materialistic.\NYou don't have to build great edifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.84,0:48:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that there's anything wrong with that, because human nature wants to put in the linear\Nworld representational.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.46,0:49:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is representational.\NOf.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.32,0:49:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Of.\NWorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.46,0:49:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great cathedrals are awesome, see.\NNational Cathedral in Washington, D.C. is an exact Gothic you'd think you were in the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.96,0:49:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,14th century in Europe.\NIncredible, because that design has come to mean devotion, dedication, worship, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.61,0:49:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Christian ideal of, the essence of Christianity.\NTo worship, so it is a symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.32,0:49:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So.\NIn and of itself, then, it represents an expression, an art form.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.51,0:49:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Architecture is an art form.\NNon-temporality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.38,0:49:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality.\NEquality means this understanding that all of life is equally of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.38,0:50:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So during lunchtime we went out in the back, and here was a stunning, I guess what the\Nworld would call a weed or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.42,0:50:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And both of us looked at it, and its perfection was incredible.\NAnd little berries in the middle of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.11,0:50:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the perfection, the presence of divinity as perfection.\NIn all that exists, it's not exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.11,0:50:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual truth is not provable.\NProof belongs to the world of cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.05,0:50:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian paradigm.\NIt can be demonstrated, it can be verified, but you cannot prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.51,0:50:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become it.\NYou can calibrate the likelihood of its presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.94,0:50:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That still doesn't prove, prove.\NSo proof is a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.03,0:50:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond 500, you can't really prove anything anymore.\NYou can only become it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.84,0:50:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove love.\NYou can't prove love.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.96,0:51:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You become loving, and it's your experience, your reality.\NBut you can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.67,0:51:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So 500 and up is not provable.\NIt's beyond proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.73,0:51:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mystical.\NWhat does mystical work mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.05,0:51:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It means it did not come about as a consequence of the Newtonian cause and effect.\NImprobable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.17,0:51:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlikely.\NStatistical likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.69,0:51:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mystical is sort of a kicked about word.\NIn its true meaning, it means to realize from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.67,0:51:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is mysterious to the intellect, but not to the mystic.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.67,0:51:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's mystical, mysterious to the mystic is how people could still fall for the sequential\Nlinearity of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.84,0:51:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo the mystic then has a tradition in Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.40,0:52:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There are the great mystics that are revered.\NMysticism, if you look it up in the Dictionary, the Encyclopedia, a lot of the phenomena that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.59,0:52:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced and I describe in various books is the very same.\NThe various ailments that come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.59,0:52:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the higher you get, the more they can be.\NLike all your nerves are on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.82,0:52:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I warn people of that too.\NOnce you decide to drive the whole way, the nervous system is not used to handling energies
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.88,0:52:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of that dimension.\NDon't forget these are logarithmic progressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.61,0:52:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Logarithmic.\NSo the difference between 785 and 790.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.96,0:52:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N785 and 790 is considerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.05,0:52:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And at about 850, it becomes quite a challenge.\NWhich we wrote about in this new book, how to handle those levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.11,0:53:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everybody here is going to be enlightened, I'm telling you about it now.\NDon't worry about it when you get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.82,0:53:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is a sensation like you're burning from within.\NI'll tell you how to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.13,0:53:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that.\Nfrom what level on you're pulling up from the collective
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.32,0:53:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,unconscious of mankind. It's not your personal\Nkarma anymore. It's not your stuff. You already
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.17,0:53:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cleared that already.\NYou start pulling from the collective
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.88,0:53:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,over 700, over\N750,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.38,0:53:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,800.\NYou start pulling from the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.80,0:53:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,collective from over 650,\N660.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.73,0:53:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in there?\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.96,0:53:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you see you've already\Ncleared all this stuff in yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.46,0:53:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. So it's a\Nmystification. Why am I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.13,0:53:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing this pain?\NAny kind of a spiritual error brings up pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.94,0:54:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're holding\Nsomething somewhere in your consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.03,0:54:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not aligned with the absolute truth,\Nit brings up pain. That forces
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.32,0:54:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you to go within and ask God,\NAlmighty God, creator of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.15,0:54:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and all things visible and invisible,\Nyou are the son of the Lord Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.75,0:54:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray that you will\Nbring forth into my awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.34,0:54:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is that\Nis not aligned with truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.05,0:54:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Something will come out\Nof some archetype deeply buried
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.17,0:54:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the collective unconscious.\NAnd in my own experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.65,0:54:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nspiritual night was the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.17,0:54:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,toughest.\NThe spiritual night kept coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.71,0:54:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be burning all over.\NI'd forgiven everything
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.94,0:54:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,decades ago. What am I indignant\Nabout? All of a sudden, like a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.53,0:54:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,rage, an indignation\Nat the violation of the truth of God
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.63,0:54:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,came up over and over.\NMan, it practically fried my nervous
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.30,0:54:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,system to death.\NIndignation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.55,0:55:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at the desecration\Nof truth
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.40,0:55:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and the glee at doing\Nso, that was bad
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.90,0:55:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,enough. But then the agreement\Nof large percentage of the population
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.78,0:55:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with it was what brought up the outrage.\NHad a heck of a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.53,0:55:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a personal me, which has long\Nsince given it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.34,0:55:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But beyond a certain level,\Nyou're like bringing it up
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.67,0:55:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for the collective consciousness\Nof mankind, as described by Carl Jung.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.15,0:55:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see, the\Ncalibrated level of consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.19,0:55:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,has slowly been rising. Not slowly,\Nbeen rising rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.40,0:55:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because each being of advanced\Nawareness now begins to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.28,0:55:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,take responsibility for some\Nportion of the collective.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.17,0:55:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember it being volitional. I'll have to look\Ninto that. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.05,0:55:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\Nlaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.88,0:55:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,odd illnesses and strange\Npassing phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.25,0:56:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly get red and hot and\Nsweat and your nervous system goes to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.25,0:56:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the blink. So with prayer\Nthen, you sort of become aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.82,0:56:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not within the\Nintellectual domain. You wake up
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.11,0:56:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the morning and you suddenly see\Nwhat it is. You see what it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.15,0:56:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is. You see what it is.\NThat if I was really a warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.82,0:56:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth, I would be\Ndefending their right
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.69,0:56:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to forgiveness instead\Nof making them wrong. You see a
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.03,0:56:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,different kind of an understanding will come up.\NAnd all of a sudden, the energy disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.96,0:56:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you may be okay for days, weeks,\Nhours, and it may start again.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.98,0:56:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm just telling you. And the\NBuddha wrote about it. As I said, when it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.96,0:56:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,became severe, we were in Korea.\NAnd Susan pulled out of the side
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.09,0:56:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,table, opened it to\Nthe Buddha. And the Buddha said his bones
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.94,0:56:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,felt like his bones were\Ncracked. And I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.11,0:56:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa, yeah, right.\NAnd then it was okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.96,0:57:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So now\Nwhat holds people at the various
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.07,0:57:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness levels is\Nusually a duality. There
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.13,0:57:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is an attraction and an aversion.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.46,0:57:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway to enlightenment is constantly\None of surrendering
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.92,0:57:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,both attractions and aversions.\NThe attraction is to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.71,0:57:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,off. Every ego position\Nhas a payoff. The
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.30,0:57:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,payoff of feeling right.\NThe indignity of my
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.78,0:57:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual night.\NThe desecration of what they've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.15,0:57:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They've grown\Nup the great Buddha of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.67,0:57:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Afghanistan. I mean, one thing\Nafter another, these people were like
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.48,0:57:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,pushing you to see how far they could\Npush you. So
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.48,0:57:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to\Ngive up that indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.51,0:57:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The pleasure of that indignation.\NAnd the seduction
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.69,0:57:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of it. You see the seduction of being\Nright. And
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.73,0:58:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender to\Nhumility. With
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.03,0:58:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,humility and the surrender then,\Nthere comes a realization
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.94,0:58:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of a different dimension.\NAnd that realization
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.42,0:58:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is of a different dimension\Nand it's beyond the duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.78,0:58:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond the duality.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.96,0:58:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you evolve then, you're lifting others.\NEach one
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.65,0:58:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,lifts the other.\NSo what can people do to help
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.34,0:58:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the people that are downtrodden in the world\Nand all? Aside from
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.32,0:58:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the physical support\Nand very obvious things
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.42,0:58:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do, is\Nby our combined intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.23,0:58:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,by that which we have become,\Nwe lift the level of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.84,0:58:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We all lift the level\Nof the sea. And as the level
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.84,0:58:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sea rises, it lifts\Nup all the ships on the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.67,0:58:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the consciousness\Nlevel of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.94,0:59:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,went from one,\NI forget what it was, over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.46,0:59:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the\Nlate 80s, it suddenly jumped
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.90,0:59:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from, I think, 190.\NYeah, 190. It was stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.40,0:59:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was stuck at 190 for many centuries.\NAnd then suddenly in the late 80s
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.84,0:59:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,went, bang, up to 205.\NThen in
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.76,0:59:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,October, I think it was last year,\Nit suddenly went to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.94,0:59:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the sea is rising.\NThe consequence of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.98,0:59:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,being rising, however,\Nis that it precipitates catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.98,0:59:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the place.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.80,0:59:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At 190, Enron wouldn't have fallen\Nin a rule of calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.38,0:59:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At 205, it falls.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.28,0:59:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The payola works\Nuntil you're
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.40,0:59:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,at the level of integrity.\NNow payola doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.67,0:59:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to the clink.\NPoor Liddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.03,0:59:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NSo here are the,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.98,1:00:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we put them as the classic dualities.\NWe could,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.51,1:00:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, spend a lecture on any one\Nof them. We all like
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.71,1:00:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is familiar and secure.\NAnd we don't want to really make a change.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.59,1:00:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a resistance to change.\NSo here's the attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.84,1:00:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be where I'm familiar.\NI want things to stay the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.48,1:00:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really\Ndon't want to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.82,1:00:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,change. That applies\Nto you as a person.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.09,1:00:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI don't really want to give up being a pickpocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.67,1:00:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I had\Nto do that in France in one lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.78,1:00:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up being a pickpocket.\NBoy, I was good at it, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.46,1:00:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Clever pickpocket.\NAnd they still play the same
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.44,1:00:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,games that we used to play.\NSo this is familiar
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.23,1:00:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,way of life, and you've got to change.\NThe attraction is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.09,1:01:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore clinging to things\Nand the fear of the new.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.80,1:01:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Even\Nspiritual work brings up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.15,1:01:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as much as you don't like\Na certain way of being, nevertheless
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.19,1:01:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's familiar, habitual.\NAnd there's a certain comfort in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.26,1:01:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And one has to then surrender that.\NBecause this way is easy,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.40,1:01:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and this one seems to take effort.\NSeems to take effort
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.26,1:01:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to correct myself.\NEvery time I make the same
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.48,1:01:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,mistake, put it in the wrong place,\NI have to now put the effort forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.67,1:01:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't go on the third shelf,\Nit goes on the second shelf.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.98,1:01:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However,\Nafter a couple of times, you automatically put it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.30,1:01:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the right place. In the end, it's rewarding.\NBecause it increases
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.63,1:01:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,your pride.\NNow, the attraction of pride is,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.01,1:01:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the energy\Nof the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.23,1:01:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these so-called negatives,\Nit isn't what they are,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.48,1:02:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the payoff\Njuice. It's the ego's
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.11,1:02:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,payola. You lack\Nthe sensation and the pleasure of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.21,1:02:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hooked on the pleasure.\NAlright, so you'll do
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.98,1:02:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,anything on the left side here\Nto get that payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.88,1:02:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll win, you'll be right, you'll be successful,\Nprove that guy wrong, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.86,1:02:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the\Npayoff is always the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.94,1:02:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so\Npride doesn't like to look
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.25,1:02:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at the possibility of humility.\NAnd it confuses
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.82,1:02:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,humility with humiliation.\NIt means to the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.69,1:02:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to be less than.\NNot realizing that humility
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.01,1:02:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to be greater than.\NGreater than.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.11,1:02:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of humility, you are greater than that.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.96,1:02:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So pride is\Nan illusion. It's a self-puffery.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.42,1:02:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the way the ego\Nkeeps going.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.40,1:02:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also can be quite proud of its\Nhumility, as we all know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.86,1:03:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the\Naspects of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.59,1:03:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is the substitution by\Nspiritual pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.80,1:03:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very hard for\Na group of intelligent people
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.61,1:03:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not to get some degree of it,\Nat least on the intellectual level.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.15,1:03:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard that, yes.\NI've been there, I heard that speaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.48,1:03:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Or\Na
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.23,1:03:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a\N,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.98,1:03:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they read that book, they're familiar.\NAnd of course, if you know a lot of Sanskrit,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.30,1:03:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that definitely makes you better than other people.\NA lot of Sanskrit.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.71,1:03:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NPeople like anger
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.17,1:03:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because then it gives them a false sense of strength.\NYou feel, when you feel angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.15,1:03:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal with anger puffs up.\NThe rooster puffs up, the gorilla puffs up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.32,1:03:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea is to intimidate your enemy\Nto appear stronger than you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.69,1:04:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger then, one of the things you get out of it,\None of the payoff,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.36,1:04:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is an illusion of strength.\NNow anger is not strength, as you well know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.57,1:04:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, as an opponent,\Nas an opponent,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.09,1:04:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a trick is,\Nhe didn't see that,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.30,1:04:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just got him pissed off.\NNow that I got him pissed off, I got him skewered.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.76,1:04:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the coach didn't see that.\NI tried to sneak in, to get him into anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.53,1:04:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the coach didn't see that. I tried to sneak in, to get him into anger.\NSee, the coach didn't see that. I tried to sneak in, to get him into anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.21,1:04:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in anger, I can skewer him in a second.\NIn anger, you take a position, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.44,1:04:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't take a position, you can't be hit,\Nbecause you intuitively get how he's coming at you,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.00,1:04:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you intuitively move aside.\NThe kung fu of survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.30,1:04:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to know before he strikes,\Nwhere the strike was coming from,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.03,1:05:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have to intuit what it was about you\Nthat was attracting the strike in that area.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.94,1:05:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And you pick out that you took some kind of a stance, okay?\NIt was your stance that he read,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.09,1:05:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore he came back in that space which you created, huh?\NAll right, so anger then is a weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.98,1:05:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In a combative situation,\Nother than decoy deception,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.46,1:05:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which is always worth the try,\Nyou always try to get him mad.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.76,1:05:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You kick him where the coach can't see it.\NNow you got him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.50,1:05:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes in with anger.\NHe says, gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.75,1:05:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,With anger, you skewer yourself.\NSo it is not a strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.42,1:05:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A strength is wisdom.\NAh, wisdom, that is strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.13,1:05:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy just stands there and reads you\Nbefore the bout starts.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.30,1:05:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch him.\NWatch him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.01,1:06:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I did boxing years back, you know?\NAnd if the guy's reading you, look out,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.07,1:06:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because he isn't coming on with bravado.\NHe's not coming on with anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.96,1:06:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming on with cool calculation.\NDangerous, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.61,1:06:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So strength then is staying cool.\NThe attraction here, of course, is to win,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.96,1:06:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which everybody sees as a gain,\Nand the fear, of course, is loss.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.32,1:06:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the whole world we live in,\Nthe world of gain and loss.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.53,1:06:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The stock market, everything else is win and lose.\NAll right, the other gains are feeling important.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.82,1:06:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the reasons we like to win is we feel important.\NIt gives us a temporary sense of empowerment.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.03,1:06:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Empowerment.\NThere is a legitimate side to winning as respect,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.26,1:07:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the recognition that the consequence was as a result\Nof your own dedication and effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.15,1:07:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a recognition, which is different than a vanity.\NThe attraction of money, excitement,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.55,1:07:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of desire itself, status, these are familiar,\Nand I'm working on them for the next book, because each of these,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.01,1:07:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are aligned with certain levels of consciousness.\NWe're going to stop a few minutes early,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.65,1:07:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because we don't have time for Nico to chant.\NAnd so we're going to stop at 5 or 2.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.71,1:07:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,People love opinions.\NStop any person on the street,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.32,1:07:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've got an opinion on everything.\NI remember an old friend of mine that became seriously involved
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.32,1:07:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in a recovery group, spiritual group.\NAnd he came over to my house one day, and he says,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.57,1:07:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, Dave, I've just stunned and knocked out.\NI said, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.51,1:08:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I just realized I don't have\Nto have an opinion on everything, and I feel so free.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.23,1:08:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not obligated to have one.\NI don't have to fight for one, stand for one, defend one,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.53,1:08:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,create one, position one.\NI don't need to have an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.82,1:08:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about the election?\NI don't think anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.63,1:08:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Democracy in action, how does that sound, you know?\NAbout catastrophes, well, you know, as Ramana Maharshi says,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.38,1:08:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the world you see, you think you see, doesn't even exist.\NAnd his recommendation is that you surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.52,1:08:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,His recommendation is.\NBecause you don't know what's right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.53,1:08:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what's the undoing\Nof bad karma or good karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.22,1:08:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What looks to you like a catastrophe to other people,\Nit's frankly salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.50,1:08:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's been on the edge\Nof catastrophe has been on the edge of catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.06,1:08:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's been on the edge of catastrophe has been on the edge\Nof catastrophe has been on the edge of catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.65,1:08:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, it was the edge of the catastrophe the guy should let go\Nand got you the salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.46,1:09:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that catastrophe, without your feet being held\Nto the fire, you weren't about to quit, were you?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.42,1:09:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's holding people's feet to the fire.\NIsn't God cruel?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.02,1:09:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NI remember when I became an atheist,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.28,1:09:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I went from a devout religionist,\Nas I've told you before, and walking through the woods one day,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.35,1:09:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nothing, out of nothing,\NI wouldn't think about anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.46,1:09:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,came to me the revelation of the totality\Nof the suffering of mankind throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.59,1:09:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like the opposite of what was later realized.\NIt was like it's denial or opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.69,1:09:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw the totality of the agony, the totality of the agony\Nof all of mankind's suffering over eons of time, it was staggering.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.28,1:10:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I went into like shock.\NInstantly, I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.56,1:10:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No God who allowed or created that could I worship,\Nand I became an angry atheist, angry that God could allow.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.55,1:10:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I held God responsible for what is really the consequence\Nof the human ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.38,1:10:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking at the consequences\Nof the collective human ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.72,1:10:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't looking at the divinity of creation.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.25,1:10:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego held God responsible.\NSo you see how spiritual ignorance, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.26,1:10:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we can fall into the depths.\NI was a serious atheist for 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.80,1:10:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To get out of it actually took me to the depths of the lower hells,\Nnot the hells of agony, the hells far beyond agony,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.67,1:11:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,far beyond, indescribable, which go on for eons.\NThe foreverness of hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.57,1:11:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is out of time.\NAnd out of that, a voice arose, out of somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.92,1:11:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Some good karma somewhere.\NThank you, old ancestor, for worshiping the bear God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.97,1:11:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or something, because out of somewhere,\Nthere is a God I ask him to help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.01,1:11:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came the great, incredible experience,\Nand the going through the valley of death and the death.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.98,1:11:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which you are, literally,\Ndoes die.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.82,1:11:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of that which you are does die.\NAnd that opens the opposite of that vision,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.78,1:11:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence which wipes out everything,\Nother than its own reality and truth, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.38,1:12:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so then, as a consequence of that,\Ncomes the commitment, yes, to share that which you have
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.52,1:12:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced, witnessed, can verify,\Nand willing to put your hand on the Bible about.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.42,1:12:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then to combine that with a verification coming about,\Nthrough some objective means, such as the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.06,1:12:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,utilizing the scientists, et cetera.\NIn the meantime, the personage accomplishes this
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.94,1:12:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world, and having done all that,\NI have fulfilled my dedication to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.43,1:12:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as a teacher, this day.\NYeah, I dedicate it to you, and to your obvious future,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.34,1:12:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you will be doing for others,\Nbecause it goes on and on and on and on through eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.92,1:13:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you will become will become\Nthat which triggers that which will become,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.35,1:13:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which will become, and so you'll see yourself\Nas part of the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.68,1:13:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's creation and evolution are one and the same thing.\NSo, all right, we're gonna stop, and allow a chanting,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.92,1:13:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a unique experience.\NAs you know, Niko chants the Lotus Sutra in Sanskrit.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.18,1:13:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Gives yourselves notice that your chairs\Nare just totally accepting of you, as is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.93,1:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And just lean in the, you know, open,
